(2, 1, 'History of Rock Music', 'history-of-rock-music', 0, 'rock.jpg', '<p><strong>Bangladeshi rock</strong>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<strong>Bangla rock</strong>&nbsp;originated in&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chittagong\">Chittagong</a>&nbsp;with roots in 1960s and 1970s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_and_roll\">rock and roll</a>. Bangladeshi rock music was influenced by the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/American_rock\">American</a>and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/British_rock_and_roll\">British rock and roll</a>&nbsp;music. In the 1960s,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blues_rock\">blues rock</a>&nbsp;was introduced by Zinga, The Windy Side of Care, The Lightnings, Rambling Stones etc. From early to mid 1970s&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pop_rock\">pop rock</a>&nbsp;music was introduced by&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Azam_Khan_(singer)\">Uchcharon</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Souls_(band)\">Souls</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Feedback_(band)\">Feedback</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Miles_(band)\">Miles</a>. In the 1980s number of subgenres such as&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hard_rock\">hard rock</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heavy_metal_music\">heavy metal</a>&nbsp;was introduced. In the 1990s hard rock and heavy metal broke through the mainstream with bands like&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Love_Runs_Blind\">LRB</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/James_(musician)\">Feelings</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ark_(Bangladeshi_band)\">Ark</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warfaze\">Warfaze</a>&nbsp;etc.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>In the 2000s, genres that emerged into the mainstream included&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alternative_rock\">alternative rock</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Thrash_metal\">thrash metal</a>. In the 2010s,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indie_rock\">Indie rock</a>&nbsp;went mainstream with bands like Ashes,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chirkutt\">Chirkutt</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joler_Gaan\">Joler Gaan</a>.</p>\r\n', 1, '2019-06-12 16:11:07', '2019-06-12 16:05:20'),
